ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, I would recommend this course! This course is very helpful, and also very interesting. Students can benefit a lot from this course.

This course is extremely helpful to anyone who wants to understand the basic behavior of linear systems, even if you do not know much about linear algebra, because at the beginning of the course Professor Morse will review linear algebra used in this course.
It is usefull for students who are going to do research about control theory
Because thhe topics and lectures are good.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I learn a lot of useful knowledge about control, and I also improved my mathematical skill through this course! My research is about large-scale parallel computing, and my research topic is related to control. In a word, this course helps me a lot for my research.

This course is extremely helpful to my research, because I often use linear systems as a model to formulate research problems. The properties of linear systems and approaches I learned from this course is very useful to my dissertation/research.
It helps me understand the background better
